Welcome to the basic package.

This guide will help you get started with the core concepts
and commonly used classes in this library.

## Overview

The basic package provides a variety of foundational types
that demonstrate common Dart patterns. Start by exploring
the [MyClass] and [Color] types, which cover the most
frequently used features.

## Quick Start

1. Import the library: `import 'package:basic/basic.dart';`
2. Create an instance of [MyClass] using one of its constructors
3. Use the [Color] enum to work with color values
4. Explore the other types as needed

## Next Steps

Once you are familiar with the basics, check out the
Utilities category for helper classes and functions
that build on top of these core types.

## Elements in this category

### Classes

- [MyClass](basic/MyClass/MyClass.md)
### Enums

